[[File:Westway Retail Park sign in Wardpark, Cumbernauld - geograph.org.uk - 1311397.jpg|thumb|right|Westway Retail Park, Wardpark near [[Castlecary]]]]'''Wardpark''' is an industrial estate in [[Cumbernauld]], [[Scotland]] split by the [[M80 motorway]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Wardpark Cumbernauld|url=http://www.wardparkcumbernauld.com/index.php|website=Wardpark Cumbernauld|publisher=ColeAD|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> The former [[Burroughs Corporation|Burroughs]] factory, the first factory of Cumbernauld new town, was reoccupied by [[Oki Electric Industry|OKI]] but was demolished to make way for Westway Retail Park, OKI having been relocated to [[Westfield, Cumbernauld|Westfield]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Osborn|first1=Frederic James|last2=Whittick|first2=Arnold|title=The New towns - The Answer to Megalopolis|date=1963|publisher=McGraw-Hill|location=London|pages=312-321|url=https://archive.org/stream/newtowns00osbo#page/320/mode/2up/search/old+inns|accessdate=25 October 2017}}</ref>
Warkpark is divided into three areas: '''Wardpark South''', on the [[Abronhill]] side of the M80; '''Wardpark North''' on the [[Westerwood]] side; and '''Wardpark East''' which next to it and adjacent to [[Castlecary]] village. On the aerial photo the yellow building is part of the Wardpark Studios where the [[Outlander (TV series)|Outlander TV series]] is made. It is just north of the Westway Retail Park. This film company have plans to expand in 2018.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Miller|first1=Phil|title=Analysis:Three projects in the pipeline to help productions make big picture|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/15984820.Analysis_Three_projects_in_the_pipeline_to_help_productions_make_big_picture/|accessdate=15 February 2018|publisher=Herald Scotland|date=9 February 2018}}</ref>
John G Russell Transport Limited bought one of the largest warehouses, at 5 Wardpark, early in 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=Colliers International makes flying start to 2018 with large warehouse sale|url=https://sbnn.co.uk/2018/02/01/colliers-international-makes-flying-start-2018-large-warehouse-sale/|accessdate=15 February 2018|publisher=Scottish Business News Network|date=1 February 2018}}</ref> Other businesses in Wardpark North include Teledyne Technologies,<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G67 3EN|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g68-0ef|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Aspen Solutions Ltd<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G68 0EH|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g68-0eh|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Corporate Insignia Limited,<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G68 0HH|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g68-0hh|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Thermaflow Ltd,<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G68 0LG|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g68-0lg|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Coilcraft Europe Limited,<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G68 0LL|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g68-0ll|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> and Masonary Solutions Ltd.<ref>{{cite news |title=Still a family affair for Wardpark firm |url=https://www.cumbernauld-news.co.uk/news/business/still-a-family-affair-for-wardpark-firm-1-4766201 |accessdate=9 July 2018 |agency=Cumbernauld News |date=9 July 2018}}</ref>
Wardpark South accommodates: Markon Limited,<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G68 0EF|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g67-3en|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Moulded Foams (Scotland) Ltd.,<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G67 3JZ|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g67-3jz|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Northwest Plant Limited<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G67 3EH|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g67-3eh|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref>
Wardpark East accommodates: Coronet Services Limited, <ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G68 0LN|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g68-0ln|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Polyglass (GB) Limited,<ref>{{cite web|title=Endole Suite G68 0LN|url=https://suite.endole.co.uk/explorer/postcode/g68-0lw|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref>
[[Cumbernauld Airport]] is at the northern edge of Wardpark with views down the [[Strathkelvin]] valley. The country road to the north has been blocked to motor vehicles and crosses the [[Antonine Wall]] and the main [[Glasgow]]-[[Edinburgh]] railway line before leading to the [[Forth and Clyde canal]]. [[File:Aerial_view_of_Castlecary.jpg|thumb|left|upright=2|Wardpark from the air. The [[Forth and Clyde Canal|canal]] crosses the picture bottom left to top right (west to east). The [[Edinburgh and Glasgow Railway|railway]] is just below it with the white roof of the CMS buildings at [[Castlecary]] between them. The [[Red Burn]] (SUDS) ponds can be seen south of the Arches which are just visible. Cumbernauld's Wardpark can be seen being divided by the [[M80 motorway|M80]] as it heads north towards [[Stirling]]. At the bottom left the edge of [[Westerwood]] can be seen below [[Cumbernauld Airport]]. At the bottom, the small white T-shaped building is the Old Inns petrol station which separates Castlecary Road from the M80. The curve of Forest Road round [[Whitelees]] in [[Cumbernauld]] and Whitelees Roundabout which divides it from [[Abronhill]] are at the bottom right. North of Castlecary, [[Banknock]] can be seen on the left extending towards [[Longcroft, Falkirk|Longcroft]] and [[Dennyloanhead]] with [[Denny, Falkirk|Denny]] and [[Bonnybridge]] at the top right.]] [[File:Cumbernauld Airport from the air.JPG|thumb|upright=2|left|Bottom right to top left: Wardpark, [[Cumbernauld Airport]], [[Cumbernauld#History|Arniebog Farm<ref>{{cite web|title=OS 25 inch map 1892-1949, with Bing opacity slider|url=http://maps.nls.uk/geo/explore/#zoom=17&lat=55.9749&lon=-3.9836&layers=168&b=1|website=National Library of Scotland|publisher=Ordnance Survey|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>]], [[Military Way]], Westerwood Golf Course, the [[Forth and Clyde canal]], [[Banton, North Lanarkshire|Banton Loch]] (Townhead Reservoir), the [[Campsie Fells]].]] [[File:Wardpark industrial estate, Cumbernauld. - geograph.org.uk - 128488.jpg|thumb|upright=2|left|Wardpark industrial estate, [[Cumbernauld]]]]
